iStore has revealed the official South African pricing for the new Apple MacBook Air. The new MacBook Air is now available for pre-order and will ship to customers in South Africa in mid-November. There are two models of the 13-inch laptop available on the iStore website, one with 128GB of solid state storage and the other with 256GB. Apple launched its new, thinner MacBook Air at the end of October, delivering improved performance in a more portable chassis. Key features of the new MacBook Air include improved battery life, an 8th-gen Intel Core i5 processor, and up to 16GB of DDR4 RAM. Design changes include the addition of a fingerprint sensor and a Force Touch trackpad with increased surface area. Below is the South African pricingÂ on the iStore.